<H2><SPAN=20
style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; COLOR: #0070e8; =
mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"=20
lang=3DEN-GB>The Problem</SPAN><SPAN=20
style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; =
mso-bidi-font-size: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"=20
lang=3DEN-GB><O:P></O:P></SPAN></H2>
<P>An architect wants to design a very high building. The building will =
consist=20
of some floors, and each floor has a certain size. The size of a floor =
must be=20
greater than the size of the floor immediately above it. In addition, =
the=20
designer (who is a fan of a famous Spanish football team) wants to paint =
the=20
building in blue and red, each floor a colour, and in such a way that =
the=20
colours of two consecutive floors are different.=20
<P>To design the building the architect has <I>n</I> available floors, =
with=20
their associated sizes and colours. All the available floors are of =
different=20
sizes. The architect wants to design the highest possible building with =
these=20
restrictions, using the available floors.=20
<H2><SPAN=20
style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; COLOR: #0070e8; =
mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"=20
lang=3DEN-GB>The Input</SPAN><SPAN=20
style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"=20
lang=3DEN-GB><O:P></O:P></SPAN></H2>
<P style=3D"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN=20
style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB" =
lang=3DEN-GB>The=20
input file consists of a first line with the number <I>p</I> of cases to =
solve.=20
The first line of each case contains the number of available floors. =
Then, the=20
size and colour of each floor appear in one line. Each floor is =
represented with=20
an integer between -999999 and 999999. There is no floor with size 0. =
Negative=20
numbers represent red floors and positive numbers blue floors. The size =
of the=20
floor is the absolute value of the number. There are not two floors with =
the=20
same size. The maximum number of floors for a problem is=20
500000.<O:P></O:P></SPAN></P>
<H2><SPAN=20
style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; COLOR: #0070e8; =
mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"=20
lang=3DEN-GB>The Output</SPAN><SPAN=20
style=3D"FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"=20
lang=3DEN-GB><O:P></O:P></SPAN></H2>
<P style=3D"MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN=20
